The paper focuses on improving the search functionality of geoportals using query expansion techniques to capture a user's search intention. This involves enriching a user's query from both geospatial and thematic perspectives. The paper discusses the implementation of this framework using ArcGIS Online as a case study. The paper's content is relevant to several sub-categories of computer science, including information retrieval (cs.IR), digital libraries (cs.DL), databases (cs.DB), computational linguistics (cs.CL), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
